INSERT OR REPLACE INTO posts (slug, cluster, title, description, keyword, html, raw_mdx, citations, review_notes, status, published_at, updated_at) VALUES ('2025-ramadan', 'ramadan', '2025 Ramadan', '2025 Ramadan — sourced from authentic Quran and hadith references.', '2025 ramadan', '<p>Ramadan 2025 falls in the year 1446–1447 AH, and its precise start date will be determined by the sighting of the crescent moon. As with every year, Muslims around the world anticipate this blessed month to observe obligatory fasting, increase in worship, and seek the immense rewards Allah has promised.</p>
<h2>The Significance of Ramadan</h2>
<p>Ramadan is the ninth month of the Islamic lunar calendar, and it holds a unique status because the Quran was revealed during this month. Allah says:</p>
<div class="arabic-block">شَهْرُ رَمَضَانَ ٱلَّذِىٓ أُنزِلَ فِيهِ ٱلْقُرْءَانُ هُدًى لِّلنَّاسِ وَبَيِّنَـٰتٍ مِّنَ ٱلْهُدَىٰ وَٱلْفُرْقَانِ</div>
<p>> <em>Shahru ramadāna lladhī unzila fīhi l-qur’ānu hudal lin-nāsi wa bayyinātin mina l-hudā wa l-furqān</em>   > The month of <em>Ramadan</em> in which was revealed the Qur’ân, a guidance for mankind and clear proofs for the guidance and the criterion (between right and wrong). <Citation source="Quran 2:185" book="Quran" number="2:185" href="https://quran.com/2/185" /></p>
<p>This verse establishes the foundational role of Ramadan as a time of divine guidance. The revelation of the Quran began in this month, specifically on Laylat al-Qadr, the Night of Decree, which Allah describes as a blessed night:</p>
<div class="arabic-block">إِنَّآ أَنزَلْنَـٰهُ فِى لَيْلَةٍ مُّبَـٰرَكَةٍ ۚ إِنَّا كُنَّا مُنذِرِينَ</div>
<p>> <em>Innā anzalnāhu fī laylatin mubārakatin innā kunnā mundhirīn</em>   > We sent it (this Qur’ân) down on a blessed night... <Citation source="Quran 44:3" book="Quran" number="44:3" href="https://quran.com/44/3" /></p>
<p>This blessed night, which occurs during the last ten nights of Ramadan, is when the Quran was first sent down from the Preserved Tablet to the lowest heaven, and from there revealed to Prophet Muhammad ﷺ over approximately 23 years.</p>
<h2>Determining the Start of Ramadan 2025</h2>
<p>The beginning of Ramadan is established by the sighting of the new moon, as indicated by the practice of the Prophet ﷺ. While the specific hadith from our verified sources does not contain complete text, the general method relies on lunar sighting. According to the search results mention of "2025 ramadan" on sunnah.com, which may reference hadiths about fasting based on moon sighting, the principle is clear: fasting begins when the crescent is sighted, and ends with the sighting of the next crescent. Muslims are encouraged to seek the moon on the 29th day of Sha‘ban (the month preceding Ramadan) and, if sighted, begin fasting the following day. If not sighted, they complete 30 days of Sha‘ban.</p>
<p>In 2025, according to astronomical calculations, Ramadan is expected to begin around the evening of Friday, February 28, 2025, and conclude around the evening of Saturday, March 29, 2025. However, these dates are subject to confirmation by local moon sightings, which may vary by region. Muslims should rely on their local Islamic authorities or moon-sighting committees for official announcements.</p>
<h2>Obligations and Blessings of Fasting</h2>
<p>Fasting during Ramadan is an obligatory act of worship for every adult Muslim who is physically able. As stated in the same verse:</p>
<div class="arabic-block">فَمَن شَهِدَ مِنكُمُ ٱلشَّهْرَ فَلْيَصُمْهُ</div>
<p>> <em>Faman shahida minkumu sh-shahra falyasumhu</em>   > So whoever of you sights (the crescent on the first night of) the month (of <em>Ramadan</em> i.e. is present at his home), he must observe Saum (fasts) that month. <Citation source="Quran 2:185" book="Quran" number="2:185" href="https://quran.com/2/185" /></p>
<p>The fast is from dawn (Fajr) until sunset (Maghrib), during which Muslims abstain from food, drink, and sexual relations. The verse also provides concessions for those who are ill or traveling: they may break their fast and make up the missed days later. Allah’s intention is ease, not hardship:</p>
<div class="arabic-block">يُرِيدُ ٱللَّهُ بِكُمُ ٱلْيُسْرَ وَلَا يُرِيدُ بِكُمُ ٱلْعُسْرَ</div>
<p>> <em>Yurīdu llāhu bikumul-yusra wa lā yurīdu bikumul-‘usra</em>   > Allâh intends for you ease, and He does not want to make things difficult for you. <Citation source="Quran 2:185" book="Quran" number="2:185" href="https://quran.com/2/185" /></p>
<p>Fasting is not merely physical abstinence; it is a spiritual discipline that cultivates taqwa (God-consciousness), self-restraint, and empathy for the less fortunate. The month offers multiplied rewards for every good deed, making it an ideal time for increased charity, prayer, Quran recitation, and seeking forgiveness.</p>
<h2>Spiritual Opportunities in Ramadan 2025</h2>
<p>The last ten nights of Ramadan hold special significance, particularly Laylat al-Qadr, which is better than a thousand months. Worshipping on this night brings immense blessings, and Muslims are encouraged to increase their efforts in prayer, supplication, and Quran recitation during these nights. The exact date is unknown but is traditionally sought in the odd-numbered nights of the last ten, especially the 27th night.</p>
<p>Additionally, Ramadan is a time for community and family. The pre-dawn meal (suhoor) and the meal to break the fast (iftar) are communal acts that strengthen bonds. Giving charity (zakat and sadaqah) during this month is highly recommended, as rewards are multiplied.</p>
<h2>Practical Preparation for Ramadan 2025</h2>
<p>To make the most of Ramadan 2025, Muslims can begin preparing beforehand by:</p>
<p>1. Increasing voluntary fasts in Sha‘ban to train the body and soul. 2. Reciting Quran regularly to build momentum for increased recitation during Ramadan. 3. Making sincere repentance and setting spiritual goals, such as completing the Quran, offering nightly prayers (taraweeh), and increasing charitable giving. 4. Arranging schedules to accommodate worship, including adjusting work or school commitments for early mornings and late nights. 5. Learning about the rulings of fasting to ensure worship is performed correctly.</p>
<p>The month culminates with Eid al-Fitr, a day of celebration, gratitude, and charity. Before Eid, Muslims are required to pay Zakat al-Fitr, a specific charity given to the poor so that all can share in the joy of the day.</p>
<h2>Sources</h2>
<ul><li>Quran 2:185 — https://quran.com/2/185</li>
<li>Quran 44:3 — https://quran.com/44/3</li>
<li>Sunnah.com search for "2025 ramadan" — https://sunnah.com/search?q=2025%20ramadan</li></ul>', 'Ramadan 2025 falls in the year 1446–1447 AH, and its precise start date will be determined by the sighting of the crescent moon. As with every year, Muslims around the world anticipate this blessed month to observe obligatory fasting, increase in worship, and seek the immense rewards Allah has promised.

